{
    "name": "Troll Berserker",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Tactics",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Base Statistics</b> When he\u2019s not raging, the barbarian\u2019s statistics are <b>AC </b>22, touch 12, flat-footed 19; <b>hp </b>148; <b>Fort </b>+18, <b>Will </b>+3; bite +14 (1d8+7), 2 claws +15 (1d6+9); rend (2 claws, 1d6+14); <b>Str </b>25, <b>Con </b>28; <b>CMB </b>+16, <b>CMD </b>29; <b>Skills </b>Intimidate +16."
        },
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> cold mountains"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "More feral than typical trolls, ragers are bloodthirsty maniacs in battle, known for tearing off and swallowing pieces of living opponents. These trolls are the most likely to overeat and devastate the food supply in an area."
        }
    ],
